time required: 20 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/gouda-pear-and-cheddar-grilled-cheese-66e9e549dd17515898b2c7f7
---

Wash and dry produce.

Quarter, core, and thinly slice @pear{1}. Halve, peel, and finely chop half the @shallot{1}(halved, peeled, and finely chopped) (whole shallot for 4 servings). Quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{a drizzle} and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a large pan over medium heat. Add pear, shallot, @honey{2%tsp}, juice from one lemon wedge, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} (juice from two lemon wedges and 1 tsp sugar for 4). Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until pear has softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Stir in juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4). Wash out pan.

Heat pan used for pear over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%oz}(diced); cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop. Wipe out pan.

Evenly layer half the @sourdough bread{4%slices} with @gouda cheese{2%slices} and as much pear as you like. Top with @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and remaining sourdough slices to form sandwiches.

Add bacon along with gouda, pear, and cheddar.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for pear over medium heat. Once hot, add sandwiches and push around in pan until butter has absorbed. (For 4 servings, work in batches or use a second pan, using 1 TBSP butter for each batch.) Cook until bread is golden brown and cheese is slightly melted, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add another @butter{1%tbsp} to pan, then flip sandwiches and push around again until butter has absorbed. Cook until bread is golden brown and cheese is fully melted, ~{4-6%minutes}.

== Lemony Arugula & Pecan Salad ==

While sandwiches are toasting, in a #large bowl{}, whisk together juice from one lemon wedge, @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp}, and @pepper{pinch}. (For 4 servings, use juice from two wedges, 4 TBSP olive oil, and 1⁄2 tsp salt.)

Add @arugula{2%oz} and @?pecans{1/2%oz}. Toss to thoroughly coat arugula.

Halve sandwiches on a diagonal. Divide sandwiches and salad between plates. Serve.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.